Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.cache.idmapping.string

Interface Tracker

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, MemoryStatsVisitor.Visitable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTracker, BigIdTracker, IntTracker
    public interface Tracker
extends MemoryStatsVisitor.Visitable, AutoCloseable
    EncodingIdMapper is an index where arbitrary ids, be it String or long or whatever can be added and mapped to an internal (node) long id. The order in which ids are added can be any order and so in the end when all ids have been added the index goes through a prepare phase where these ids are sorted so that IdMapper.get(Object, Group) can execute efficiently later on.

    In that sorting the ids aren't moved, but instead a Tracker created where these moves are recorded and the initial data (in order of insertion) is kept intact to be able to track Group belonging among other things. Since a tracker is instantiated after all ids have been added there's an opportunity to create a smaller data structure for smaller datasets, for example those that fit inside int range. That's why this abstraction exists so that the best suited implementation can be picked for every import.
